1
00:00:10,867 --> 00:00:13,033
I know Olive very well,
she will shoot me!

2
00:00:13,167 --> 00:00:14,967
Mom! Mom! Mom!

3
00:00:15,433 --> 00:00:16,833
I'll take care of her!

4
00:00:16,967 --> 00:00:18,600
What the heck!

5
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:20,367
Why is the car stopping?

6
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:21,633
No!

7
00:00:22,367 --> 00:00:23,433
What am I going to do?

8
00:00:26,767 --> 00:00:28,167
Olive, please stop this!

9
00:00:28,300 --> 00:00:30,967
No matter where you hide,
the law will find you!

10
00:00:31,100 --> 00:00:33,100
They will never stop until they
put you back

11
00:00:33,233 --> 00:00:35,000
- in jail!
- Let me go!

12
00:00:35,833 --> 00:00:36,933
Olive!

13
00:00:37,767 --> 00:00:39,167
Come on, hold on tight!

14
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:43,233
Olive!

15
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:46,833
Help me, Olive.

16
00:00:49,400 --> 00:00:54,567
You must die.

17
00:01:39,067 --> 00:01:40,533
Hurry up! Let's go!

18
00:01:42,167 --> 00:01:43,367
Mookie.

19
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:47,067
Mom!

20
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:49,567
Mom! Dad!
What happened? Why...

21
00:01:49,700 --> 00:01:50,700
We got in an accident.

22
00:01:50,833 --> 00:01:52,433
But we're fine, Dear.

23
00:01:53,233 --> 00:01:54,133
Don't worry.

24
00:01:54,267 --> 00:01:56,700
Ma'am, how are my twins?

25
00:01:56,833 --> 00:01:58,533
Have you seen Jade and Olive?

26
00:01:59,167 --> 00:02:00,133
We haven't found them yet.

27
00:02:00,267 --> 00:02:01,833
But we're gonna look for them
inside.

28
00:02:01,967 --> 00:02:03,700
Let's go, we'll help you look
for them.

29
00:02:04,533 --> 00:02:06,533
- This way.
- This way, let's go.

30
00:02:07,133 --> 00:02:09,533
Emma, Danilo, are you guys okay?

31
00:02:09,667 --> 00:02:11,467
We're okay.
I feel a bit dizzy,

32
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:13,033
but we have to go, come on.

33
00:02:13,867 --> 00:02:15,600
- Let's go.
- Let's go, Kutsy.

34
00:02:15,733 --> 00:02:16,700
Come on.

35
00:03:00,367 --> 00:03:02,233
Thank you very much.

36
00:03:02,867 --> 00:03:04,633
Rest in peace, Jade.

37
00:03:04,767 --> 00:03:05,833
I mean...

38
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:07,900
Olive.

39
00:03:23,233 --> 00:03:24,267
Officers.

40
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:26,833
We've been searching all day.

41
00:03:26,967 --> 00:03:30,967
Perhaps we can find them faster
if we spread out?

42
00:03:31,467 --> 00:03:32,467
Okay.

43
00:03:33,833 --> 00:03:34,800
Okay.

44
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,667
Where should we start?

45
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:39,067
Let's look over there.

46
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:40,233
Yes.

47
00:03:42,867 --> 00:03:45,533
Wait a minute. Let's think first
where we're going.

48
00:03:45,900 --> 00:03:47,367
God, please help us.

49
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:50,233
Where should we go?

50
00:03:50,367 --> 00:03:51,900
Please show us the way...

51
00:03:52,033 --> 00:03:53,000
What is it, Emma?

52
00:03:53,133 --> 00:03:54,400
Look at my mom.

53
00:03:55,267 --> 00:03:56,933
She's so concerned
about the twins.

54
00:03:57,867 --> 00:03:59,700
She didn't even ask me
if I'm okay.

55
00:04:00,767 --> 00:04:02,467
Emma, try to understand her.

56
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:04,267
You're fine anyway.

57
00:04:05,767 --> 00:04:07,400
You have to understand your
mom's situation.

58
00:04:13,533 --> 00:04:15,367
God, please help me.

59
00:04:17,933 --> 00:04:19,667
Over here!
There's someone here!

60
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:21,100
Where?

61
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:22,667
Where are they?

62
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,000
They could be my children!

63
00:04:24,133 --> 00:04:26,167
Stand still, it's dangerous.

64
00:04:26,300 --> 00:04:27,500
It's quite deep.

65
00:04:27,667 --> 00:04:28,667
I need to see them!

66
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:30,267
It could be them!

67
00:04:32,633 --> 00:04:33,933
- Let me see.
- Wait, Ma'am.

68
00:04:34,067 --> 00:04:35,267
It's not safe, Ma'am.

69
00:04:35,900 --> 00:04:37,100
- Let me see!
- Is that them, Ma'am?

70
00:04:41,667 --> 00:04:43,133
Olive!

71
00:04:44,233 --> 00:04:45,900
Jade!

72
00:04:46,033 --> 00:04:47,367
Let's go to them!

73
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:48,933
We have to go down there.

74
00:04:49,067 --> 00:04:51,067
Let's go! I want to go to them!

75
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:52,967
Come on!
What are we going to do?

76
00:04:53,100 --> 00:04:54,367
They're down there...

77
00:04:54,933 --> 00:04:57,367
Jade! Olive!

78
00:04:57,500 --> 00:04:58,633
Ligaya!

79
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:02,200
Olive!

80
00:05:02,333 --> 00:05:03,467
Jade!

81
00:05:04,033 --> 00:05:05,067
Olive?

82
00:05:05,633 --> 00:05:07,800
- My child!
- Ma'am, don't touch them yet.

83
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:10,667
-Let me go!
-We have to wait for the medics.

84
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:12,733
Jade! Olive!

85
00:05:18,867 --> 00:05:20,633
Why? Wake up!

86
00:05:23,433 --> 00:05:24,400
Let me go!

87
00:05:24,533 --> 00:05:27,067
Let me go!

88
00:05:27,567 --> 00:05:29,900
Let me go!
Don't try to stop me!

89
00:05:41,900 --> 00:05:43,500
My child, wake up.

90
00:05:43,633 --> 00:05:45,567
Wake up, Olive.

91
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:48,300
Olive.

92
00:05:52,867 --> 00:05:53,767
Jade.

93
00:05:53,900 --> 00:05:55,800
Jade? My child?

94
00:05:57,767 --> 00:05:58,700
She's alive!

95
00:05:58,833 --> 00:05:59,833
She's still alive!

96
00:05:59,967 --> 00:06:01,267
She's still breathing!

97
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:03,200
Hey! Help us!

98
00:06:03,333 --> 00:06:04,767
Help my daughter!

99
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:07,933
Call for help, hurry!

100
00:06:08,100 --> 00:06:09,500
Jade...

101
00:06:14,167 --> 00:06:16,600
Olive, Jade...

102
00:06:19,167 --> 00:06:22,367
My child...

103
00:07:07,633 --> 00:07:08,900
Mom?

104
00:07:10,733 --> 00:07:12,033
Mom?

105
00:07:16,067 --> 00:07:17,167
Jade, dear?

106
00:07:18,067 --> 00:07:19,167
Mom?

107
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:21,700
How are you feeling?

108
00:07:23,733 --> 00:07:25,100
Olive?

109
00:07:27,033 --> 00:07:28,167
Your sister?

110
00:07:28,300 --> 00:07:29,867
Where is she?

111
00:07:32,867 --> 00:07:34,667
Don't be shocked, Jade.

112
00:07:36,767 --> 00:07:38,000
What?

113
00:07:38,133 --> 00:07:40,133
Olive is gone.

114
00:07:43,233 --> 00:07:45,133
Olive is dead.

115
00:07:50,033 --> 00:07:51,367
No!

116
00:07:52,300 --> 00:07:54,333
No!

117
00:07:54,467 --> 00:07:55,333
Jade.

118
00:07:55,467 --> 00:07:59,133
Olive can't die!

119
00:07:59,267 --> 00:08:02,667
Mom!

120
00:08:03,533 --> 00:08:06,100
Mom!

121
00:08:10,300 --> 00:08:13,167
Mom, my sister!

122
00:08:22,167 --> 00:08:23,800
It might be harmful to your
condition, Jade.

123
00:08:27,433 --> 00:08:29,133
It might be harmful to you.

124
00:08:33,333 --> 00:08:34,767
That's enough, Jade.

125
00:08:47,267 --> 00:08:49,733
Excuse me, Ma'am.

126
00:08:49,867 --> 00:08:51,633
- Hello.
- Miss Jade Caparas,

127
00:08:51,767 --> 00:08:53,333
can we talk to you?

128
00:08:53,467 --> 00:08:55,867
We just need to hear
your statement.

129
00:08:56,333 --> 00:08:58,067
I'm sorry,

130
00:08:58,200 --> 00:09:01,133
but can you talk to her later?

131
00:09:02,033 --> 00:09:03,367
She needs to rest.

132
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:04,600
Mom.

133
00:09:06,533 --> 00:09:07,767
It's okay.

134
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:09,467
Are you sure, Jade?

135
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,900
I don't remember...

136
00:09:20,267 --> 00:09:21,733
what happened exactly.

137
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:25,367
I just remember talking
to my sister

138
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:28,700
and asking her to surrender.

139
00:09:30,233 --> 00:09:33,267
But she doesn't want to do that.

140
00:09:37,133 --> 00:09:38,633
And then...

141
00:09:39,433 --> 00:09:40,667
she got mad at me.

142
00:09:42,967 --> 00:09:45,433
And when we were at the cliff...

143
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:53,633
She pushed me off.

144
00:09:58,067 --> 00:10:00,300
I got hold of her hand.

145
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:03,333
And then...

146
00:10:06,067 --> 00:10:08,600
we both fell off.

147
00:10:19,933 --> 00:10:24,633
Olive!

148
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:32,700
Olive!

149
00:10:33,933 --> 00:10:37,567
Mom, my sister!

150
00:10:38,100 --> 00:10:41,533
My sister is gone!

151
00:10:44,633 --> 00:10:48,933
Mom!

152
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:54,800
My sister is gone!

153
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:02,500
Ma'am, here are your belongings.

154
00:11:47,467 --> 00:11:48,433
Excuse me.

155
00:11:48,567 --> 00:11:50,367
you can now look at the remains.

156
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:52,800
Thank you.

157
00:11:53,567 --> 00:11:54,833
Mookie!

158
00:11:54,967 --> 00:11:55,967
Dear, stay here.

159
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:57,733
Why, Mom?

160
00:11:59,067 --> 00:12:00,733
I'm just trying to protect you.

161
00:12:01,333 --> 00:12:03,233
I don't want this to add to your
trauma.

162
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,200
Emma.

163
00:12:06,900 --> 00:12:08,033
Olive is dead.

164
00:12:08,933 --> 00:12:10,667
She can't harm anyone anymore.

165
00:12:11,267 --> 00:12:13,667
Mom, that won't erase the fact
that she hurt my daughter.

166
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:16,467
Why do you want her
to see her remains?

167
00:12:17,100 --> 00:12:18,500
To remind her of all the trauma

168
00:12:18,633 --> 00:12:20,000
that woman caused her?

169
00:12:22,467 --> 00:12:25,000
Emma, I understand what you're
coming from.

170
00:12:25,867 --> 00:12:29,900
I know that Olive did you wrong,
especially to Mookie.

171
00:12:31,267 --> 00:12:33,800
I'll understand if you don't
want Mookie

172
00:12:33,933 --> 00:12:36,467
to be around on her wake.

173
00:12:38,167 --> 00:12:39,667
We're not gonna be there either.

174
00:12:40,333 --> 00:12:41,367
What?

175
00:12:42,967 --> 00:12:44,100
Come on, Emma.

176
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:46,433
Olive is my daughter.

177
00:12:46,567 --> 00:12:47,800
She's your sister.

178
00:12:48,833 --> 00:12:50,733
If you can't accept her
as your sister,

179
00:12:50,867 --> 00:12:53,300
please respect her
as a human being.

180
00:12:53,433 --> 00:12:54,467
She's gone now!

181
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:57,833
No, Mom.

182
00:12:57,967 --> 00:12:59,567
She never accepted you.

183
00:13:00,267 --> 00:13:02,500
And she stole our daughter.

184
00:13:02,633 --> 00:13:04,833
Mookie almost died because of
the experiments

185
00:13:04,967 --> 00:13:06,333
Olive did on her.

186
00:13:06,467 --> 00:13:08,867
And you want me to forget what
happened now that she's dead?

187
00:13:12,833 --> 00:13:14,867
I'm sorry, Jade, but my
daughter's connection

188
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:17,000
with your twin ends here.

189
00:13:18,067 --> 00:13:19,767
And her connection with you too.

190
00:13:19,900 --> 00:13:20,833
Let's go.

191
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,200
- Emma.
- Let's go home.

192
00:13:23,067 --> 00:13:24,600
Emma, wait.

193
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:56,400
Emma, it's Olive's burial.

194
00:13:56,533 --> 00:13:58,000
Let our daughter see her
for the last time.

195
00:13:58,133 --> 00:14:01,067
Since you didn't let
her go to Olive's wake.

196
00:14:02,367 --> 00:14:04,567
You know the reason why.

197
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:06,767
Emma, you're not protecting
Mookie,

198
00:14:06,900 --> 00:14:09,667
you're depriving her of her
right to see...

199
00:14:09,800 --> 00:14:12,300
To see the woman
who tortured her?

200
00:14:12,433 --> 00:14:14,567
Dan, she did Mookie wrong.

201
00:14:32,833 --> 00:14:34,233
How are you?

202
00:14:37,133 --> 00:14:38,100
Oh wow.

203
00:14:39,300 --> 00:14:40,767
That looks good!

204
00:14:47,033 --> 00:14:49,600
Sweetie....

205
00:14:49,733 --> 00:14:50,667
I'm sorry...

206
00:14:52,333 --> 00:14:54,400
if we didn't go
to Olive's wake.

207
00:14:55,933 --> 00:14:57,600
Your mom doesn't want us to go.

208
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:00,033
But...

209
00:15:03,133 --> 00:15:05,133
do you want to go
to her burial?

210
00:15:10,267 --> 00:15:13,333
I want to see her.

211
00:15:18,967 --> 00:15:21,833
I understand why Mom
doesn't want me to go.

212
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:26,267
And I respect her decision.

213
00:15:29,233 --> 00:15:30,600
But you know, Grandmother...

214
00:15:32,500 --> 00:15:34,467
I just feel guilty.

215
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:39,600
Emma, Mookie has been with
Olive for seventeen years.

216
00:15:40,567 --> 00:15:42,300
You must respect the dead.

217
00:15:42,933 --> 00:15:44,300
Why? When Olive was alive

218
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:47,900
did she respect our daughter,
did she respect us?

219
00:15:48,033 --> 00:15:48,700
No!

220
00:15:49,833 --> 00:15:52,600
I don't think it's disrespectful
to keep my daughter

221
00:15:52,733 --> 00:15:55,200
from the person who took
my right to be a mother

222
00:15:55,333 --> 00:15:56,700
for seventeen years.

223
00:15:58,133 --> 00:16:00,533
Despite everything she did
to me,

224
00:16:02,167 --> 00:16:02,733
to us,

225
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:09,200
she's still my mom.

226
00:16:12,267 --> 00:16:14,733
And I can't change that.

227
00:16:18,467 --> 00:16:21,933
We've been together for so long.

228
00:16:25,467 --> 00:16:27,767
And even though

229
00:16:27,900 --> 00:16:31,333
there were times that she hurt
me over and over,

230
00:16:32,633 --> 00:16:35,167
she's still a big part of me,
Grandmother.

231
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:41,133
And I will never stop
loving her.

232
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:43,967
That's why...

233
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:48,233
I want to go to her wake.

234
00:16:49,433 --> 00:16:51,167
To see her one last time.

235
00:17:06,133 --> 00:17:07,333
Hello?

236
00:17:09,267 --> 00:17:10,567
Hello?

237
00:17:10,700 --> 00:17:12,500
Auntie, customer!

238
00:17:12,633 --> 00:17:14,800
- I have to go somewhere.
- Hello!

239
00:17:14,967 --> 00:17:16,200
- Wait a minute.
- I want to buy something.

240
00:17:16,333 --> 00:17:18,200
Auntie, customer!

241
00:17:19,467 --> 00:17:23,133
- Hello?
- Let me do it. Wait a minute.

242
00:17:23,267 --> 00:17:24,500
I want to buy something.

243
00:17:24,633 --> 00:17:27,533
- What is it?
- How much for that color green?

244
00:17:27,667 --> 00:17:29,500
The color blue? Ten pesos.

245
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:34,700
Because it's two pieces,
that would be 10 pesos.

246
00:17:34,833 --> 00:17:37,400
Emma, I understand
why you're mad.

247
00:17:37,533 --> 00:17:39,900
But did you ask Mookie
what she wants?

248
00:17:40,033 --> 00:17:42,867
Did you ask how she feels?

249
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:45,100
Did she not want
to see Olive?

250
00:17:47,833 --> 00:17:49,433
Emma.

251
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:50,567
Mookie?

252
00:17:57,333 --> 00:17:58,367
Mookie?

253
00:18:00,633 --> 00:18:01,600
Mookie?

254
00:18:02,233 --> 00:18:03,333
Dan!

255
00:18:03,467 --> 00:18:06,100
- What?
- Mookie's gone.

256
00:18:06,233 --> 00:18:07,900
Look, why is her stuff her?

257
00:18:09,733 --> 00:18:10,767
Dan!

258
00:18:10,900 --> 00:18:13,533
- What?
- Mookie's gone!

259
00:18:13,667 --> 00:18:15,233
Look, this is her stuff.

260
00:18:16,833 --> 00:18:19,067
Wait, she probably
just went somewhere.

261
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:21,167
Someone could have
kidnapped Mookie!

262
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:22,967
Emma, who would kidnap her?

263
00:18:23,133 --> 00:18:24,267
Olive's people!

264
00:18:25,300 --> 00:18:26,967
Olive is gone.
How is that possible?

265
00:18:27,100 --> 00:18:28,967
What if she told her people to
take Mookie

266
00:18:29,100 --> 00:18:30,267
no matter what happens?

267
00:18:32,567 --> 00:18:34,067
- Wiro, have you seen Mookie? -
Here's Wiro.

268
00:18:34,200 --> 00:18:35,367
She was just here earlier.

269
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:37,267
She's with Ligaya.

270
00:18:37,633 --> 00:18:39,100
I saw them get
in a car earlier.

271
00:18:39,233 --> 00:18:40,267
They get in a car?

272
00:18:57,900 --> 00:18:59,300
Here we are.

273
00:18:59,433 --> 00:19:04,400
Zayn, thank you for helping us.

274
00:19:04,533 --> 00:19:05,467
You're welcome.

275
00:19:07,367 --> 00:19:10,267
Grandmother, my mom
might get mad.

276
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:11,700
Don't worry,

277
00:19:12,500 --> 00:19:13,700
she won't get mad.

278
00:19:14,833 --> 00:19:16,433
As long as she won't find out.

279
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:31,600
Good morning, my dear family!

280
00:19:31,767 --> 00:19:33,900
How are you?

281
00:19:34,033 --> 00:19:35,333
I can't wait to show you

282
00:19:35,467 --> 00:19:38,467
what I have in store
for all of you!

283
00:19:38,600 --> 00:19:39,933
Are you all ready?

284
00:19:40,067 --> 00:19:44,533
Cause I am so ready!

285
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:52,600
Hi, Jade.

286
00:19:52,733 --> 00:19:56,000
I have been practicing
to be like you.

287
00:19:56,133 --> 00:19:59,267
And look, I've mastered it.

288
00:20:05,133 --> 00:20:06,200
They got in a car?

289
00:20:06,333 --> 00:20:07,667
Who kidnapped them?

290
00:20:07,800 --> 00:20:09,067
Calm down...

291
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:12,867
okay? Just calm down.
You're a bit too exaggerated.

292
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:14,367
It was Zayn.

293
00:20:14,500 --> 00:20:18,433
Ligaya asked him to bring
them to Olive's burial.

294
00:20:19,867 --> 00:20:20,267
What?

295
00:20:43,733 --> 00:20:44,933
Emma, sweetie?

296
00:20:45,067 --> 00:20:46,233
What's going on? Why?

297
00:20:46,367 --> 00:20:47,800
Hello, Mom.

298
00:20:47,933 --> 00:20:51,200
I know that you took
Mookie to Olive's burial.

299
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:52,667
Wiro told me.

300
00:20:52,800 --> 00:20:54,033
Can you go home now?

301
00:21:06,633 --> 00:21:09,500
Grandmother, I think we
should head home.

302
00:21:09,667 --> 00:21:11,967
My mom might get mad.

303
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:14,400
I don't care.

304
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:18,733
She can be mad at me.
She can fight me.

305
00:21:21,333 --> 00:21:25,900
This is my last chance
to see my oldest daughter.

306
00:21:28,667 --> 00:21:31,067
I will never see her again.

307
00:21:43,200 --> 00:21:45,533
You're so stupid, Jade.

308
00:21:47,500 --> 00:21:49,667
If you sided with me,

309
00:21:51,033 --> 00:21:53,500
you wouldn't be
where you are now.

310
00:21:55,700 --> 00:21:56,467
Too bad.

311
00:21:58,633 --> 00:22:00,100
But don't worry.

312
00:22:02,367 --> 00:22:06,733
Now I have more reason
to take revenge on Emma...

313
00:22:08,333 --> 00:22:10,300
because you got caught
in our feud.

314
00:22:13,167 --> 00:22:14,967
I will make sure...

315
00:22:16,600 --> 00:22:23,567
that I slowly send Emma
to her grave.

316
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:27,733
So...

317
00:22:29,600 --> 00:22:30,567
thank you...

318
00:22:31,500 --> 00:22:33,533
for my new identity, Jade.

319
00:22:34,833 --> 00:22:35,867
Don't worry.

320
00:22:37,300 --> 00:22:39,600
I will make sure...

321
00:22:39,733 --> 00:22:43,000
your sacrifice
won't be in vain.

322
00:22:44,467 --> 00:22:46,767
No one else will know.

323
00:22:48,033 --> 00:22:49,333
It's between you and me.

324
00:22:50,867 --> 00:22:51,833
Olive?

325
00:23:06,300 --> 00:23:08,367
You have to find
a new apartment.

326
00:23:08,500 --> 00:23:12,633
My new tenant has already paid
six months in advance.

327
00:23:12,767 --> 00:23:14,567
And she paid double for it.

328
00:23:14,700 --> 00:23:16,767
No matter where you go.

329
00:23:18,067 --> 00:23:19,467
I will make sure

330
00:23:20,033 --> 00:23:22,767
that you'll end up with me,
Emma.

331
00:23:25,567 --> 00:23:27,733
- Thank you so much.
- You're welcome.

332
00:23:27,867 --> 00:23:28,967
Danilo!

333
00:23:29,100 --> 00:23:30,033
This is for you!

334
00:23:30,167 --> 00:23:32,500
Welcome to your new house, Emma.

335
00:23:32,633 --> 00:23:35,200
This time, I wouldn't
just take Mookie from you.

336
00:23:35,333 --> 00:23:37,733
I will take everyone
that you love.

337
00:23:37,867 --> 00:23:39,533
You're extraordinary, Jade!

338
00:23:39,667 --> 00:23:42,367
Miss Generosity of the year!

339
00:23:42,500 --> 00:23:46,367
I want to thank you
for letting us live here.

340
00:23:46,500 --> 00:23:48,333
I've been dreaming of this.

341
00:23:48,467 --> 00:23:50,133
To be with you,
all my children.

342
00:23:50,267 --> 00:23:55,433
Just enjoy your happy moments
while you still can, Emma.

343
00:23:55,600 --> 00:23:58,200
This won't last long.
